# SQL DISTINCT

## What Is It?

DISTINCT is used to remove duplicate values from the result set.

It returns only unique records.

---

## Why Do We Use It?

In real-world databases, duplicate values are common.

It helps:

- Remove duplicates
- Find unique values
- Improve reporting accuracy
- Explore data quickly

---

## Syntax

```sql
SELECT DISTINCT column_name
FROM table_name;
```

---

## Example

Find all unique specializations.

```sql
SELECT DISTINCT specialization
FROM Doctors;
```

