## Interview Question

### Q: What is the difference between COUNT(Column) and COUNT(DISTINCT Column)?

count(column) counts every row including the ones with null values 
and duplicate entries

count(distinct column) counts only unique, non-null values present in the specific column

## Common Mistake

Wrong:

```sql
SELECT DISTINCT *
FROM Patients;
```

Using DISTINCT on all columns may not remove duplicates if even one column value differs.

Better:

```sql
SELECT DISTINCT city
FROM Patients;
```

Use DISTINCT only on the columns where uniqueness is required.

